<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="flesh-n">flesh <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /fleʃ/    美 /fleʃ/  </p>
<p>[U]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>肉；(人体的) 皮肤；(果、菜) 的可食用部分：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Tigers are <strong>flesh-eating</strong> animals. 
老虎是肉食动物。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In some Middle Eastern countries, exposing your flesh is forbidden, especially if you are a woman. 
在一些中东国家，禁止露出皮肤，尤其是女性。</p><footer>2014 重庆</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The spirit is willing, but <strong>the flesh</strong> is weak.
心有余而力不足。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="flesh-and-blood">flesh and blood</h3>
<p>1.<strong>血肉之躯</strong>  </p>
<h3 id="in-the-flesh">in the flesh</h3>
<p>1.<strong>亲自；本人：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We won't have to go there in the flesh at all!
我们无需亲自前往！</p><footer>北师大② – 4</footer></div></div>